2026-05-17 06:35:17 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #4 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Compute freshwater beach exceedance rate by year (2020-2023) from water-body-testing files; interpret 'Violation' as exceedance, using Violation column; compute summer rainfall totals Jul-Aug-Sep using monthly_precipitations_boston; impute missing monthly precipitation values with each month's median across available years; then compare year-to-year increase/decrease patterns between exceedance rates and summer totals.", "dataset_id": "kramabench-environment-hard-18", "code": "import pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport numpy as np\nbase='/home/ec2-user/eval_eqa/exploratory-qa-eval/.sandbox_isolated/task_1676744_1778999688841'\nfiles={\n'2020':f'{base}/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2020.csv',\n'2021':f'{base}/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2021.csv',\n'2022':f'{base}/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2022.csv',\n'2023':f'{base}/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2023.csv',\n'precip':f'{base}/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/monthly_precipitations_boston.csv'\n}\n\ndef exceed_rate(path,year):\n    df=pd.read_csv(path)\n    # freshwater beach filter\n    # Beach Type Description may contain 'Freshwater' or 'Freshwater ' etc.\n    df['Beach Type Description']=df['Beach Type Description'].astype(str)\n    fr=df[df['Beach Type Description'].str.contains('Freshwater',case=False,na=False)]\n    # Violation indicates exceedance\n    v=fr['Violation']\n    fr_ex=(v.astype(str).str.strip().str.lower().isin(['yes','y','true','1']))\n    # if NO/No etc\n    rate=fr_ex.mean() if len(fr_ex)>0 else np.nan\n    n_total=len(fr_ex)\n    return rate,n_total\n\nrates={}\nfor y in ['2020','2021','2022','2023']:\n    r,n=exceed_rate(files[y],int(y))\n    rates[int(y)]=r\n\nprec=pd.read_csv(files['precip'])\nprec.columns=prec.